      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">15/6/88 ¶ Private ¶  ¶ Two letters from you, esteemed Mr Tepper, lie before me; ¶ Letters not found. ¶  ¶ I will answer the important one first. There seem to be several applicants for the position of...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">88.06.15</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Tepper</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M198, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">15/6/88</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Privat</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Zwei Briefe von Ihnen, geehrter Herr Tepper, liegen mir vor; den wichtigen will ich zuerst beantworten. Es scheinen mehrere Bewerber um die Stelle eines Entomologen zu sein, aber wenn eine solche überhaupt vom Parlament genehmigt wird, kann schwerlich jemand ausserhalb Victoria auf der Erlang rechnen, denn es ist hier ein starkes Gefühl gegen den Berufung von Staats Beamten aus anderen Colonien, da man denkt, dass unter der Millionen von Bewohnern dieser Colonie genug sind, um irgend eine Stelle auszufüllen. Dies Gefühl hat sich besonders bei der Besetzung der Stelle des Försters kundgegeben.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Die Vergebung der Stelle ist in einem andere Ministerial Departement als dem, welchem ich angehöre, so kann ich nicht einmal Einfluss auf die Wahl ausüben.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ihr kleiner Band über die Insekten Süd Australiens ist ausgezeichnet, u sollte viele neue Beobachter hervorrufen. Während der nächsten Monate dürfen Sie nicht viel rechnen auf Hülfe von mir. Die Vorbereitungen für die Welt-Ausstellung nehmen jede Freie Stunde in Anspruch.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Sie ehrende der</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Postscript begins below valediction but completed in the margins of this page and the preceding one.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Einige Pflanzen will ich für Sie immer benennen. Wenn Sie anstatt der andern Touren eine zum Murray machten um an der Grenze von Vict. Wasserpfl. &amp;c zu sammeln so möchten Sie Neues sowohl für S.A. als V. entdecken. Ihnen ist der untere Murray mehr zugänglich als aus hier.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Additional text on a separate page.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">16/6/88</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sollte sich in Bezug auf die Besetzung der Stelle hier etwas ereignen, das für Sie günstig sein möchte, so würde ich Ihr Interesse wahrnehmen.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Von der Great bend bis zur Vict. Grenze sollten noch reiche Fundstellen für Pflanzen sein, besonders an den Lagunen u im Sandland u Salzland.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15/6/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Private</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Two letters from you, esteemed Mr Tepper, lie before me;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letters not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I will answer the important one first. There seem to be several applicants for the position of entomologist, but if anyone<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at all<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is approved by Parliament, someone outside Victoria can hardly reckon upon succeeding, since there is a strong feeling here against the appointment of state officials from other colonies since it is thought that there are enough among the millions of inhabitants of this Colony to fill any position. This feeling was revealed particularly in the case of the filling of the position of forester.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>George Perrin, who was the Tasmanian Conservator of Forests, was appointed as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Victoria's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Conservator of Forests<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>23 June 1888 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Victoria Government<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">g</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">azette</seg>, 29 June 1888, p. 2070), but the appointment had been announced in May (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Age</seg>, 12 May 1889,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>p. 9).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The gift of the position is in a ministerial department other than that to which I belong, so I cannot even exert influence on the choice.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's assistant<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Charles French Snr<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was appointed Victoria's Government<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Entomologist<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1889, in the Office of Agriculture (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Victoria Government<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">g</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">azette</seg>, 25 October 1889, p. 3641). The Minister had indicated that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he intended to appoint from within the Public Service, and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>only if the Public Service Board reported that ‘there is no gentleman possessing the necessary qualifications will he advertise for applicants’ (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Australasian</seg>, 19 May 1889, p. 18).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your small volume on the insects of South Australia<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Tepper (1887-90), vol.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is excellent and should give rise to many new observers. During the next few months you should not count on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>much<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>help from me.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The preparations for the International Exhibition<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Centennial International Exhibition. Melbourne, 1888-9.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>claim every free hour.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I will always name some plants for you. If instead of other tours you made a tour to the Murray to collect water plants &amp;c at the boundary of Victoria, you might discover new things for South Australia as well as for Victoria. The lower Murray is more accessible to you than<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>us here.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">16/6/88</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Should anything happen in respect to the appointment to the position here that may be favourable for you, I would look after your interest.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>From the Great Bend<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Of the Murray<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>River<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>where, at Morgan, SA, the direction of flow changes from predominantly east-west to north-south.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to the Victorian border there should be rich localities for plants, particularly on the lagoons and in the sandy country and salt country.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
